#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_3614347\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_3614347\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Juni 26, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104lhc1665702761265.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/lhc1665702761265.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/lhc1665702761265.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"lhc1665702761265\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">catch\n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"lhc1665702761265__catch_211331\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">In a <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">try...endtry</span> block, introduces the code to catch and handle exceptions.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"lhc1665702761265__topic_d69995e1_d69996e1_d69997e1\">\n<div class=\"p\">\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104lhc1665702761265_html_0\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"lhc1665702761265__codeblock_kfh_qvz_bwb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">try\n    &lt;ProcScript that may throw an exception&gt;\n{catch} {ErrorNumber1 {,ErrorNumberN}}\n    &lt;Procscript that handles the error &gt;\nendtry</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"lhc1665702761265__topic_d45897e1_d45898e1_d45899e1_d45900e1_d45901e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d686261e69\">\n                       \n Parameters\n </h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"3\" id=\"lhc1665702761265__d6838e20\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Parameters</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"lhc1665702761265__d6838e20__entry__1\">\n Parameter\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"lhc1665702761265__d6838e20__entry__2\">\n Data Type\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"lhc1665702761265__d6838e20__entry__3\">\n Description\n </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lhc1665702761265__d6838e20__entry__1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">ErrorNumbers</var>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lhc1665702761265__d6838e20__entry__2\">\n Numeric\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lhc1665702761265__d6838e20__entry__3\">\n A comma-separated list of error numbers that the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">catch</span> statement will catch.\n <p class=\"p\">If omitted, the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">catch</span> block catches any exception.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"lhc1665702761265__topic_d45902e1_d45903e1_d45904e1_d45905e1_d45906e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d686261e132\">Return Values</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"lhc1665702761265__d5995e20\">None</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"lhc1665702761265__topic_d45907e1_d45908e1_d45909e1_d45910e1_d45911e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d686261e141\">Use</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"lhc1665702761265__d5916e20\">Allowed in all component types.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"lhc1665702761265__topic_d45912e1_d45913e1_d45914e1_d45915e1_d45916e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d686261e151\">\n                       \n Description\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"lhc1665702761265__p_d70019e1_d70020e1_d70021e1\">For each <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">try</span> declaration, it is possible to have multiple <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">catch</span> statements to test for specific errors. The <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">endtry</span> command must come after the last <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">catch</span> statement.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"lhc1665702761265__p_d70022e1_d70023e1_d70024e1\">Each <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">catch</span> block catches only the exceptions that are specified in its comma-separated list of arguments. If there are multiple catch blocks, they are processed in order.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"lhc1665702761265__p_d70025e1_d70026e1_d70027e1\">If you specify a <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">catch</span> statement without arguments, it must be the last <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">catch</span> block because it catches any exception.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"lhc1665702761265__p_d70028e1_d70029e1_d70030e1\">Within a <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">catch</span> block, the error\n            information is available in <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$procerror</span> and\n               <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$procerrorcontext</span>. For example, the following code puts a message\n            in the message frame if an exception is thrown when calling the Do_It function:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">trigger detail\n try\n call Do_It()\n catch\n putmess \"An error occurred: %%($procerror): %%($procerrorcontext)\" \n endtry\nend</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"lhc1665702761265__p_d70031e1_d70032e1_d70033e1\">This error information is not available outside the specific catch block.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"lhc1665702761265__p_d70034e1_d70035e1_d70036e1\">A catch block can also contain a <code class=\"ph codeph\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"bzp1665702760995.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/bzp1665702760995.html\" title=\"Rethrows an exception that was caught in a catch block.\">rethrow</a>\n</code>statement. This allows you to rethrow an exception that was caught in the\n               <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">catch</span> block.</p>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"lhc1665702761265__note_w1884ab1b5c11c17_w1885ab1b5c11_w1886ab1b5_w1887ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span>  A\n               <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">catch</span> block can also throw an exception. In this case, the\n            exception will bubble up to a higher level.</div>\n<p class=\"p\">The goto statement and ProcScript label are not allowed inside a catch block, and will\n            result in a compilation error.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"lhc1665702761265__p_d70037e1_d70038e1_d70039e1\">For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"rue1665702683651.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rue1665702683651.html\" title=\"Exceptions are abnormal runtime events that may occur after executing a software instruction. Uncaught exceptions cause code execution to stop and the application to exit with a description of the error and where it occurred.\">Exception Handling</a> and <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"sal1665702761072.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/sal1665702761072.html\" title=\"A try block specifies a ProcScript instruction, or set of instructions, that could raise an exception.\">try</a>.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rue1665702683651.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Exception Handling</a><p>Exceptions are abnormal runtime events that may occur after executing a software instruction. Uncaught exceptions cause code execution to stop and the application to exit with a description of the error and where it occurred.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/sal1665702761072.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>try</a><p>A try block specifies a ProcScript instruction, or set of instructions, that could raise an exception.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/mrq1665702761335.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>endtry</a><p>Defines the end of a try...endtry block used to handle exceptions.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/nab1665702580017.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>finally</a><p>Declares ProcScript inside a try-endtry block that must be executed, regardless of whether an exception occurs or not.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/bzp1665702760995.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>rethrow</a><p>Rethrows an exception that was caught in a catch block.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3614347\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3614347\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "catch Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Juni 26, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 catch In a try...endtry block, introduces the code to catch and handle exceptions. Explain this code try <ProcScript that may throw an exception> {catch} {ErrorNumber1 {,ErrorNumberN}} <Procscript that handles the error > endtry Copy Parameters Table 1. Parameters Parameter Data Type Description ErrorNumbers Numeric A comma-separated list of error numbers that the catch statement will catch. If omitted, the catch block catches any exception. Return Values None Use Allowed in all component types. Description For each try declaration, it is possible to have multiple catch statements to test for specific errors. The endtry command must come after the last catch statement. Each catch block catches only the exceptions that are specified in its comma-separated list of arguments. If there are multiple catch blocks, they are processed in order. If you specify a catch statement without arguments, it must be the last catch block because it catches any exception. Within a catch block, the error information is available in $procerror and $procerrorcontext . For example, the following code puts a message in the message frame if an exception is thrown when calling the Do_It function: trigger detail try call Do_It() catch putmess \"An error occurred: %%($procerror): %%($procerrorcontext)\" endtry end Copy This error information is not available outside the specific catch block. A catch block can also contain a rethrow statement. This allows you to rethrow an exception that was caught in the catch block. Note: A catch block can also throw an exception. In this case, the exception will bubble up to a higher level. The goto statement and ProcScript label are not allowed inside a catch block, and will result in a compilation error. For more information, see Exception Handling and try . Related Links Exception Handling Exceptions are abnormal runtime events that may occur after executing a software instruction. Uncaught exceptions cause code execution to stop and the application to exit with a description of the error and where it occurred. try A try block specifies a ProcScript instruction, or set of instructions, that could raise an exception. endtry Defines the end of a try...endtry block used to handle exceptions. finally Declares ProcScript inside a try-endtry block that must be executed, regardless of whether an exception occurs or not. rethrow Rethrows an exception that was caught in a catch block. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}